{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GToggleNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This functionality is intended for binding ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to a proxy"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object managed by another memory manager. This is done with two"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"paired references: the strong reference added by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"text":" and a reverse reference to the proxy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object which is either a strong reference or weak reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The setup is that when there are no other references to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only a weak reference is held in the reverse direction from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the proxy object, but when there are other references held to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":", a strong reference is held. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"type":"text","text":" callback is called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when the reference from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"text":" to the proxy object should be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“toggled” from strong to weak ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"is_last_ref"},{"type":"text","text":" true) or weak to strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" false).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since a (normal) reference must be held to the object before"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"text":", the initial state of the reverse","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"link is always strong."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple toggle references may be added to the same gobject,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"however if there are multiple toggle references to an object, none"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of them will ever be notified until all but one are removed.  For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this reason, you should only ever use a toggle reference if there","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is important state in the proxy object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if you unref the object on another thread, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"type":"text","text":" might"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"still be invoked after "},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and the object argument"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"might be a dangling pointer. If the object is destroyed on other threads,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you must take care of that yourself.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be released with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLibObject","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE12addToggleRef6notify4datayySvSg_SpySo8_GObjectVGSgs5Int32VtXCSg_AGtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject14SignalGroupRefV","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addToggleRef"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and another reference is established.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SignalGroupRef"}],"title":"SignalGroupRef","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SignalGroupRef","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSignalGroup"},{"text":" manages a collection of signals on a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupRef/addToggleRef(notify:data:)":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)","abstract":[{"text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and another reference is established.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addToggleRef"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref\/objectprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations"}}}